mount /dev/sda5 -o uid=1000,gid=100,umask=022 /media/fermat/
mount /dev/sda6 -o uid=1000,gid=100,umask=022 /media/gauss/


To produce linearized PDFs in linux, use the following "FastWebView" switch in gs:

gs -dFastWebView=true -dNOPAUSE -dBATCH -sDEVICE=pdfwrite -sOutputFile=output.pdf input.pdf 

This is useful for uploading to some journals, which for some reason only accept linearized pdfs. (Another way is to open the file in Adobe Acrobat and save it once.) 